                    <h4 class="content-subhead">M-Q-T-What?</h4>

                    <h3>For the "Internet of Things".</h3>
                    <p>
			<a class='jlink' href="http://mqtt.org">MQTT</a> is a
			machine-to-machine connectivity protocol which was
			designed as a very lightweight publish/subscribe
			messaging transport. It is very useful for connections
			with remote locations (such as from a mobile device)
			where network bandwidth is at a premium.  MQTTitude
			uses the MQTT protocol to safely transmit your location
			information to your server which, in MQTT terms, is called a
			"broker".
		    </p>
